      NFT Stuff
   =20
 =20
A non-fungible token is, at a minimum, a bit of code that lives on a blockc=
hain that you can =E2=80=9Cown.=E2=80=9D When I put it like that it isn=E2=
=80=99t very appealing. When I add that the code can  point to a web server=
 that hosts a JPEG image, it =E2=80=A6=C2=A0doesn=E2=80=99t sound that much=
 more appealing? You =E2=80=9Cown=E2=80=9D the JPEG in some very specific b=
lockchain-y sense, but you don=E2=80=99t actually own it, and anyone else c=
an look at it or download it.But this is dumb and trivializing, and=C2=A0re=
ally=C2=A0what an NFT is is a symbol of membership in some sort of online (=
or offline) community. The best and most valuable NFTs offer their owners r=
eal=C2=A0social=C2=A0benefits; owning an NFT in a popular series like Crypt=
oPunks or Meebits gives you a sense of community, perhaps some=C2=A0intelle=
ctual-property rights, and a way to socialize with like-minded, uh, venture=
 capitalists.Owning an NFT in the Bored Ape Yacht Club series gives you a p=
articularly valuable social experience: You get to have your Bored Ape stol=
en and then complain about it online, which lets you feel a sense of kinshi=
p with  Seth Green and a bunch of venture capitalists who have also had the=
ir Bored Apes stolen.Here, for instance, is=C2=A0a New York Times story abo=
ut apes getting stolen on the NFT trading platform OpenSea. And here is the=
 latest ape theft:The Bored Ape Yacht Club (BAYC) Discord server was hacked=
 on Saturday, with the attacker making off with 200 ETH ($360,000) worth of=
 NFTs, according to Yuga Labs.The hack took place after the project=E2=80=
=99s community manager, Boris Vagner, had his Discord account compromised, =
which the attacker then used to post phishing links in both the official BA=
YC and its related metaverse project called Otherside=E2=80=99s Discord cha=
nnels.Yeah one lesson here is that there is absolutely no link that the mem=
bers of the BAYC Discord server won=E2=80=99t click. They just love clickin=
g links! =E2=80=9CMaybe this is the link that will get my ape stolen,=E2=80=
=9D they hope, and this weekend they were right.Look, this is what Bored Ap=
e=C2=A0Yacht Club is! Bored Ape Yacht Club is a way to spend a lot of money=
 to become the victim of an online theft that you can then complain about! =
You are not getting some other utility from pretending to own a picture of =
a monkey! But once it is stolen you can commiserate with Seth Green or what=
ever.=C2=A0
