om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">This again</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">No, come on, stop it. Six weeks ago, E=
lon Musk <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27964259.=
265611/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQt=
MjcvYmlsbC1od2FuZy1hcnJlc3QtaW5zaWRlLXRoZS12aWNpb3VzLWN5Y2xlLW9mLWFyY2hlZ29=
zLWNvbGxhcHNlP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA2MDYyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdX=
RtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDYwNiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzd=
HVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2956ef96" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> signed a merger agreeme=
nt</a> in which he made a legally binding promise to=C2=A0buy Twitter Inc. =
for $54.20 per share. A few weeks later, he decided he didn=E2=80=99t want =
to pay $54.20 per share anymore, perhaps because he had grown=C2=A0bored of=
 Twitter, or=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
27964259.265611/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzI=
wMjItMDUtMTcvZWxvbi1tdXNrLWRvZXMtbm90LWNhcmUtYWJvdXQtc3BhbS1ib3RzP2NtcGlkPU=
JCRDA2MDYyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0d=
GVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDYwNiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a=
319a23cBc042e6db" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"=
_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;">perhaps=C2=A0because</a> the prices of social-med=
ia stocks, and of Musk=E2=80=99s company Tesla Inc., had fallen, and $54.20=
 looked pretty expensive.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The merger agreem=
ent does not, however, allow Musk to walk away because he changed his mind.=
 He needed some pretext for walking away. He <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/27964259.265611/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNv=
bS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDUtMTMvZWxvbi1tdXNrLXRyb2xscy10d2l0dGVyP2N=
tcGlkPUJCRDA2MDYyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZX=
dzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDYwNiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef=
4b8524a319a23cB3b012acb" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" tar=
get=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; b=
order-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style:=
 solid; background-color: #ccc;"> came up with</a> what he thought was a go=
od one: Twitter says, in its public filings, that no more than 5% of its =
=E2=80=9Cmonetizable daily active users=E2=80=9D are =E2=80=9Cfalse or spam=
=E2=80=9D accounts, and Musk has a vague sense that there are more spam bot=
s than that. (To be fair, a lot of <em>his=C2=A0</em>followers <a href=3D"h=
ttps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27964259.265611/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3=
cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9lbG9uLW11c2tzLWJvdC1wcm9ibGVtLW9uLXR3aXR0ZXItaXMtZ=
Xh0cmFvcmRpbmFyeS0xMTY1NDQyNjgwMD9tb2Q9aHBfbGlzdGFfcG9zNA/607f07ceef4b8524a=
319a23cB08a6d77d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"=
_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;">are bots</a>.) He floated the idea that he could =
walk away from the deal because Twitter was lying about the spam bots.</p><=
p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">To a non-lawyer I suppose this looked like a go=
od pretext, but it was not. It was not for at least three reasons:</p><ol s=
tyle=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<=
li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Musk had not a shred =E2=80=94=C2=A0not ev=
en the tiniest bit =E2=80=94=C2=A0of evidence that Twitter=E2=80=99s estima=
tes are wrong, and it <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cl=
ick/27964259.265611/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdHJhdGVjaGVyeS5jb20vMjAyMi9tdXNrLXR3aXR0ZXI=
tYW5kLWJvdHMtYm90LWV4cGVyaWVuY2UtYm90LXNjaWVuY2Uv/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB=
97265cda" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" =
style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wi=
dth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgro=
und-color: #ccc;"> seems very likely</a> that they are right.[1]</li>=09<li=
 style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Even if Twitter=E2=80=99s=C2=A0estimates are=
 wrong, Musk could not get out of the merger agreement unless the error was=
 likely to have a =E2=80=9Cmaterial adverse effect=E2=80=9D on Twitter=E2=
=80=99s business, and it absolutely would not.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-b=
ottom: 5px;">Musk has been talking about Twitter=E2=80=99s bot problem fore=
ver, and in fact he originally said that he wanted to buy Twitter <em>in or=
der to=C2=A0</em>fix the bot problem, so no one could possibly believe him =
when he said that he wanted to walk away from the deal because he just disc=
overed that Twitter has a bot problem.</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;=
">So there were a few days when everyone talked about how Musk was trying t=
o back out of the agreement, and about what Twitter could do to stop him, a=
nd then that died down=C2=A0when everyone realized that this pretext was te=
rrible.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/27964259.265611/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9=
vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDUtMTcvZWxvbi1tdXNrLWRvZXMtbm90LWNhcmUtYWJvdX=
Qtc3BhbS1ib3RzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA2MDYyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmd=
XRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDYwNiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlz=
dHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cCc042e6db" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> wrote at the time</a>:<=
/p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">While Musk has tweeted about no=
t going ahead with the deal, and talked about it at a private conference fo=
r his fans, it doesn=E2=80=99t seem like he has sent any formal notice to T=
witter saying that the deal is off. (Certainly neither Musk nor Twitter hav=
e made any SEC filings about that sort of notice, which you might expect if=
 he=E2=80=99d sent one.) Perhaps his lawyers are less willing to ignore the=
 agreement than he is, or at least need a better pretext than he=E2=80=99s =
managed so far.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Well. I guess =
he set his lawyers =E2=80=94 led by Mike Ringler of Skadden, Arps, Slate, M=
eagher &amp; Flom LLP =E2=80=94=C2=A0to work finding a pretext that they co=
uld stomach. And they found one, and today they filed it with the US Securi=
ties and Exchange Commission, in the form of <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/27964259.265611/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNo=
aXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIyMDY4MzQ3L3RtMjIxNzc2MWQxX2V=
4OTktby5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB13991e83" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" item=
scope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">a letter to Twitter=
 threatening to call off the deal</a>.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Thei=
r pretext is sort of the lawyer version of Musk=E2=80=99s pretext. The prob=
lem, say the lawyers, is=C2=A0not that Twitter has too many spam bots. The =
problem is that, when Musk asks for <em>information=C2=A0</em>about the spa=
m bots, Twitter doesn=E2=80=99t give him the information he wants. From the=
ir letter:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Twitter has, in fact=
, refused to provide the information that Mr. Musk has repeatedly requested=
 since May 9, 2022 to facilitate his evaluation of spam and fake accounts o=
n the company=E2=80=99s platform. Twitter=E2=80=99s latest offer to simply =
provide additional details regarding the company=E2=80=99s own testing meth=
odologies, whether through written materials or verbal explanations, is tan=
tamount to refusing Mr. Musk=E2=80=99s data requests. Twitter=E2=80=99s eff=
ort to characterize it otherwise is merely an attempt to obfuscate and conf=
use the issue. Mr. Musk has made it clear that he does not believe the comp=
any=E2=80=99s lax testing methodologies are adequate so he must conduct his=
 own analysis. The data he has requested is necessary to do so.</p></blockq=
uote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is a technical bit of mergers-and-a=
cquisitions lawyering here that might be worth explaining. In the merger ag=
reement, Twitter makes=C2=A0<em>representations</em>, statements about its =
business that it promises are=C2=A0true. Arguably one of them is something =
to the effect of =E2=80=9Cnot much more than 5% of our monetizable daily ac=
tive users are spam bots.=E2=80=9D[2] Musk thinks, or says he thinks, that =
this representation is not true. But even if he=E2=80=99s right, he can=E2=
=80=99t get out of the deal, unless it is untrue and would have a =E2=80=9C=
material adverse effect=E2=80=9D on Twitter=E2=80=99s business. If in fact =
90% of Twitter=E2=80=99s users are bots, it knows that, and it has been lyi=
ng to advertisers for years, then, uh, sure, maybe. But in any plausible ca=
se, there will not be an MAE, so=C2=A0he still has to close the deal and pa=
y $54.20 per share. Merger agreements are written this way <a href=3D"https=
://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27964259.265611/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dG=
VyLmNvbS9Bbm5NTGlwdG9uL3N0YXR1cy8xNTI3MjAzNjMzNTk4NzAxNTY5/607f07ceef4b8524=
a319a23cBecb45c59" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D=
"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;">so that</a> buyers can=E2=80=99t change their mi=
nds and come up with some trivial pretext =E2=80=94=C2=A0some tiny error in=
 the representations =E2=80=94=C2=A0to get out of the deal.</p><p style=3D"=
margin: 16px 0;">But in the merger agreement, there are also=C2=A0<em>coven=
ants</em>, promises that Musk and Twitter make to each other about what the=
y will do going forward, between the signing of the merger agreement and th=
e closing. If Twitter breaches a=C2=A0<em>representation</em>, Musk still h=
as to close unless the breach causes a material adverse effect.[3]=C2=A0But=
 if Twitter breaches a=C2=A0<em>covenant</em>, Musk can walk away: He doesn=
=E2=80=99t have to close unless Twitter =E2=80=9Cshall have performed or co=
mplied, in all material respects, with its obligations required under this =
Agreement.=E2=80=9D[4] There is no MAE requirement: You just have to comply=
 with the covenants.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And one of the=C2=A0co=
venants=C2=A0is that Twitter =E2=80=9Cshall ... furnish promptly to [Musk] =
all information concerning the business, properties and personnel of [Twitt=
er] as may reasonably be requested in writing, in each case, for any reason=
able business purpose related to the consummation of the transactions conte=
mplated by this Agreement.=E2=80=9D[5] Another one is that Twitter will =E2=
=80=9Cprovide any reasonable cooperation reasonably requested=E2=80=9D in c=
onnection with Musk=E2=80=99s debt financing.[6]</p><p style=3D"margin: 16p=
x 0;">Musk, as a non-lawyer, came up with a pretext that is like =E2=80=9CT=
witter told me something untrue about its bot problem, so I can walk away.=
=E2=80=9D That sounds like it might work, but doesn=E2=80=99t work. But Mus=
k=E2=80=99s=C2=A0<em>lawyers=C2=A0</em>have a better pretext. It=E2=80=99s =
something like =E2=80=9Ckeep asking them for more information about their b=
ot problem; eventually you=E2=80=99ll ask questions they won=E2=80=99t answ=
er, and=C2=A0<em>then=C2=A0</em>you can walk away.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"=
margin: 16px 0;">So they write:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"=
>Under various terms of the merger agreement, Twitter is required to provid=
e data and information that Mr. Musk requests in connection with the consum=
mation of the transaction. =E2=80=A6 Mr. Musk is entitled to seek, and Twit=
ter is obligated to provide, information and data for, inter alia, =E2=80=
=9Cany reasonable business purpose related to the consummation of the trans=
action=E2=80=9D (Section 6.4). Twitter must also provide reasonable coopera=
tion in connection with Mr. Musk=E2=80=99s efforts to secure the debt finan=
cing necessary to consummate the transaction, including by providing inform=
ation =E2=80=9Creasonably requested=E2=80=9D by Mr. Musk (Section 6.11). ..=
.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As Twitter=E2=80=99s prospective owner, M=
r. Musk is clearly entitled to the requested data to enable him to prepare =
for transitioning Twitter=E2=80=99s business to his ownership and to facili=
tate his transaction financing. To do both, he must have a complete and acc=
urate understanding of the very core of Twitter=E2=80=99s business model=E2=
=80=94its active user base.=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px =
0;">And then they threaten that Musk will walk away if he doesn=E2=80=99t g=
et the information he wants:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ba=
sed on Twitter=E2=80=99s behavior to date, and the company=E2=80=99s latest=
 correspondence in particular, Mr. Musk believes the company is actively re=
sisting and thwarting his information rights (and the company=E2=80=99s cor=
responding obligations) under the merger agreement. This is a clear materia=
l breach of Twitter=E2=80=99s obligations under the merger agreement and Mr=
. Musk reserves all rights resulting therefrom, including his right not to =
consummate the transaction and his right to terminate the merger agreement.=
</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The letter does not say what =
information Musk wants=C2=A0=E2=80=94=C2=A0it references previous letters, =
dated May 25 and May 31, asking for the information, but those have not bee=
n made public =E2=80=94=C2=A0but it makes it clear that Musk is not looking=
 for information about how Twitter came to its conclusion that fewer than 5=
% of monetizable daily active users are bots. He is not looking to understa=
nd or test Twitter=E2=80=99s methodology. Instead, he wants to =E2=80=9Ccon=
duct his own analysis,=E2=80=9D which I would think would require=C2=A0raw =
data about Twitter=E2=80=99s users. Last month Twitter Chief Executive Offi=
cer Parag Agrawal <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
27964259.265611/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9wYXJhZ2Evc3RhdHVzLzE1MjYyMzc1ODA=
2Mzg4NTkyNjc/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf5e007f8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" item=
scope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">tweeted a thread</a=
> about how Twitter does this analysis, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/27964259.265611/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9wYXJhZ2Evc=
3RhdHVzLzE1MjYyMzc1ODcwODU0NjM1NTM/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBfb835a3a" itemp=
rop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc=
;">noting that</a>=C2=A0Twitter =E2=80=9Cuses both public and private data =
(eg, IP address, phone number, geolocation, client/browser signatures, what=
 the account does when it=E2=80=99s active=E2=80=A6) to make a determinatio=
n.=E2=80=9D Presumably if Musk wants to =E2=80=9Cconduct his own analysis,=
=E2=80=9D he will want the same sorts of identifiable private data that Twi=
tter uses.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Again, I don=E2=80=99t know exac=
tly what he=E2=80=99s asking for, but in general I can understand why Twitt=
er would be nervous about sharing user data with Musk. For one thing, there=
 are all sorts of regulatory and risk reasons to be nervous about sharing u=
ser data with someone who, for now at least, does not work at Twitter. For =
another thing, Musk has been publicly trolling Twitter about the bot proble=
m, and about everything else, for weeks now, and there=E2=80=99s no reason =
to think he would be particularly responsible with=C2=A0<em>this=C2=A0</em>=
information. His lawyers write:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"=
>Mr. Musk will of course comply with the restrictions provided under Sectio=
n 6.4, including by ensuring that anyone reviewing the data is bound by a n=
on-disclosure agreement, and Mr. Musk will not retain or otherwise use any =
competitively sensitive information if the transaction is not consummated.<=
/p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But this is not much comfort, =
because Musk has constantly ignored the restrictions of the merger agreemen=
t, including by <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27=
964259.265611/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwM=
jItMDQtMjcvYmlsbC1od2FuZy1hcnJlc3QtaW5zaWRlLXRoZS12aWNpb3VzLWN5Y2xlLW9mLWFy=
Y2hlZ29zLWNvbGxhcHNlP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA2MDYyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1=
haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDYwNiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW=
9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC2956ef96" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" item=
scope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> tweeting disparagi=
ng things</a> about Twitter.=C2=A0He himself has <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27964259.265611/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9l=
bG9ubXVzay9zdGF0dXMvMTUyNTYxNTg0OTE2NzU4OTM4MA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB057=
