5px;">Revlon</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In 2020, Citigroup Inc. accidentally p=
aid off $900 million of Revlon Inc.=E2=80=99s debt. Citi was the administra=
tive agent on a Revlon loan, it was doing a restructuring transaction for R=
evlon, it hit the wrong button and paid off the loan out of its own money. =
Oops! It asked for the money back, but for a variety of unusual reasons man=
y of the lenders refused. So Citi sued them, and last year, in a somewhat s=
hocking decision, a judge <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.co=
m/click/27964259.265611/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGl=
jbGVzLzIwMjEtMDItMTcvY2l0aS1jYW4tdC1oYXZlLWl0cy05MDAtbWlsbGlvbi1iYWNrP2NtcG=
lkPUJCRDA2MDYyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzb=
GV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDYwNiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8=
524a319a23cBb84e1bbe" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> said they could keep the money</a>. Citi app=
ealed, and might still win =E2=80=94=C2=A0the appeal is still pending =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0but for now Citi is out about $500 million.=C2=A0</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One strange aspect of this case is that =E2=80=A6=C2=
=A0nobody knows what happened to the loan? Citi just paid people $500 milli=
on for no reason, which is hard to fit into conventional analyses of how de=
bt works. Like:</p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40p=
x; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Does Revlon still =
owe the original lenders that $500 million, even though Citi already paid t=
hem? (After all,=C2=A0<em>Revlon=C2=A0</em>didn=E2=80=99t pay them.)</li>=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Does Revlon owe <em>Citi=C2=A0</em>tha=
t $500 million? After all, Citi did Revlon the (completely unasked-for) fav=
or of paying off its loan for it, so surely Revlon owes Citi something for =
that.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Does Revlon not owe the mone=
y to anyone? Is that $500 million debt gone?</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 1=
6px 0;">I suppose this will be clarified at some point, but the problem is =
perhaps <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27964259.2=
65611/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9yZXZsb24taW4tdGFsa3Mtd2l0aC1sZ=
W5kZXJzLWFib3V0LWV4dGVuZGluZy1kZWJ0LWRlYWRsaW5lcy0xMTY1NDI2NTI5Nz9tb2Q9aXRw=
X3dzaiZydT15YWhvbw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB76090ada" itemprop=3D"StoryLink=
" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">becoming more=
 urgent</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Cosmetics maker Re=
vlon Inc. has begun talks with lenders ahead of looming maturities of debt =
to try to steer the business clear of bankruptcy, according to people famil=
iar with the matter.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A group of lenders inc=
luding Angelo Gordon, Glendon Capital Management LP and King Street Capital=
 Management are in restructuring discussions with Revlon about pushing out =
the due date on roughly $1.7 billion in debt that matures as early as 2024,=
 people familiar with the matter said. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16p=
x 0;">The continuing debt talks are at early stages, coming more than a yea=
r before the company=E2=80=99s next significant maturity in September 2023.=
</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The 2023 loan is held by a separate group =
of lenders that were accidentally paid off by the loan=E2=80=99s agent bank=
, Citigroup Inc., in a back-office blunder, but who then gave the money bac=
k at the bank=E2=80=99s request. Others kept roughly $500 million of the mi=
staken payment and remain locked in litigation with Citi. =E2=80=A6</p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If Citibank loses its appeal, it also could seek r=
epayment of the loan from Revlon by the September 2023 maturity date, a per=
son familiar with the matter said. But Citi=E2=80=99s legal rights to seek =
repayment on the loans at maturity are murky, other people said.=C2=A0</p><=
/blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We have talked=C2=A0around here ab=
out <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27964259.26561=
1/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtMDcvZ=
GlzdHJlc3NlZC1kZWJ0LWRlYWwtbWFrZXMtcGVvcGxlLW1hZD9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNjA2MjJfTU9O=
