yMjA2MDYmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB91ed5a2a"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;"> the basic move in modern distressed-debt investing</a>, which is =
for a company to extract value from some lenders and give some of it to oth=
er lenders in exchange for them approving the transaction. If you have $2 b=
illion of debt, you promise holders of $1.1 billion of the debt that you wi=
ll pay them 105 cents on the dollar, and in exchange they approve a transac=
